solution.p:
Note that the constants have been rounded to four decimal places. To find a model for the original data \left( x, y \right), we express the equation \ln \left( y \right) = 0.0144x + 1.4112 in exponential form as follows:

  \ln \left( y \right) \amp = 0.0144x + 1.4112
  y \amp = e^{0.0144x + 1.4112}
  y \amp = e^{0.0144x} \cdot e^{1.4112}
  y \amp = 4.10e^{0.0144x}

