solution.p:
The residuals indicate that the linear fit for \left( \ln \left( x \right) , \ln \left( y \right) \right) is good, so we conclude that the original ordered pairs \left( x , y \right) can be modeled by a power function. We can find the equation of the power function by solving for y in the least squares line determined earlier.


  \ln \left( y \right) \amp = 2.4926 \ln \left( x \right) - 7.4415
  y \amp = e^{2.4926 \ln \left( x \right) - 7.4415}
  y \amp = e^{2.4926 \ln \left( x \right)} \cdot e^{-7.4415}
  y \amp = e^{-7.4415} \cdot e^{\ln \left( x^{2.4926} \right)}
  y \amp = 0.0005864x^{2.4926}


 shows a graph of this power function superimposed on the original ordered pairs. The residuals indicate that this function does a good job of modeling the relationship betwee tree age and volume

